This stage improved my understanding of how Python can process and analyse real financial data.

One challenge I encountered was handling CSV loading correctly in Google Colab. I experienced file path issues when trying to load the transaction dataset directly from GitHub. After debugging the issue, I switched to manually uploading the CSV file into Colab, which solved the problem.

This experience helped me better understand how file handling works in notebook environments and why testing file paths is important during development.

